I just made this for my son's 4th b-day party. He saw the picture on the cover of Gourmet and wanted it for his cake! I baked both the cupcakes and cake yesterday and did the buttercream and decorating today. I love to bake so I was in my elememt, but it was a little time consuming. The frosting took a while to beat, but tasted wonderful. I used the clear vanilla extract(artificial, but I wanted it white) and I also added a little Wilton white color, and the frosting was a beautiful white. The dots were fun and very festive looking. I only had trouble keeping the chocolate crumbs out of my white icing. The cake and cupcakes were both good, not dry at all. Just watch your baking time. I also added Fioro de Sicilia Orange/vanilla flavor in place of the vanilla in the cupcake batter. I am loving that stuff!! They have it in the Baker's Catalogue. Is great in batters, icings, anywhere you would use vanilla and it tastes like dreamsicle! Yum! But, amnyway, this recipe is fun and good and I will most likely do it or at least the buttercream again! Much, much better than Crisco...yuck!

