The cake was good but the frosting was very hard to work with. Just after making the frosting it was perfect... then I followed the suggestion of refrigerating it. Bringing it to room temp took about 6 hours, at which time the frosting was oddly chunky and waxy and would not spread on the cake. I re-beat it with the addition of a little powdered sugar and then it was fine. Everyone loved the taste of the frosting but I am not sure it was worth it! The different colored dots was very fun for my daughter to do.

