Rating: 3
I haven't made this cake but have made the frosting before. I had no problems with it and it came out a very light off white. One tip is to add the butter very slowly and wait at least a minute between each addition. The more air is incorporated, the lighter the frosting will be. It takes a long time - probably at least 20 minutes to add the butter. but it is worth it, in my opinion. The crisco frosting can't even be compared- waxy, nasty and flavorless. gross stuff. It's true, kids probably won't care, but I personally would rather make a whipped cream frosting than feed my kids crisco. If you want your frosting whiter, just add some of the wilton opaque white color. it will lighten it up for ya!

