Rating: 2
This issue arrived the day before New Year's Eve, my son's birthday. so, naturally, he loved the cover and wanted it for his birthday. No problem. Except that it is virtually impossible to add a pound of butter to any meringue and have it stay white, as the picture suggests. So the icing is actually almost yellow, which means it does not look like the cover. Don't even get me started on duplicating the colors of the cupcakes. I am reasonably confident the stylists at Gourmet spent considerably longer on this project than the recipes suggest. That said, there's nothing about a pound of butter that doesn't taste good.